{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784606534518,"sessionID":"ses_07d2d6659ffe0JNz4C04306Spy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_r8IieWYirdtYwp7HlAKP4359","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/spec.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Feature Specification: repo-wide kebab-case (hyphen) filesystem-naming convention\"\n3: description: \"Ban snake_case in filesystem names repo-wide and make kebab-case (hyphens) the sole canonical form for folder names, file names, and script filenames — with a hard exemption for Python (.py, PEP-8 snake_case) plus vendored/third-party trees, generated/lockfile output, tool-mandated filenames, and Python import-package directories. Code identifiers, JSON/YAML/TOML keys, frontmatter fields, and DB columns are OUT of scope (idiomatic case, hyphens illegal there). Reverses and supersedes the 027 underscore migration, including the sk-doc validator/loader logic keyed on feature_catalog / manual_testing_playbook. Phase parent for a 12-phase program (000-011): worktree + immutable-baseline + census first, then policy + all-consumer logic + create-generators + no-new-snake guard + rename-and-reference tooling + a frozen bijective rename map + shared cross-cutting closures, then a per-component migration fan-out, then alias-removal, the whole-repo gate, and integrate-latest + closeout. Migration runs on a dedicated worktree pinned to an immutable BASE SHA.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"hyphen naming convention\"\n6:   - \"kebab-case filesystem names\"\n7:   - \"ban snake_case files and folders\"\n8:   - \"reverse underscore migration\"\n9:   - \"hyphenate folder and file names\"\n10: importance_tier: \"critical\"\n11: contextType: \"planning\"\n12: parent: \"sk-doc\"\n13: _memory:\n14:   continuity:\n15:     packet_pointer: \"sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention\"\n16:     last_updated_at: \"2026-07-20T10:42:52Z\"\n17:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n18:     recent_action: \"Registered follow-on phase 012 in the parent phase map\"\n19:     next_safe_action: \"Generate 012 child metadata, then validate 012 and the parent\"\n20:     blockers: []\n21:     key_files: []\n22:     completion_pct: 0\n23:     open_questions: []\n24:     answered_questions:\n25:       - \"Scope = filesystem names only (folders/files/script filenames); code identifiers + JSON/YAML/TOML keys + frontmatter fields keep idiomatic case\"\n26:       - \"Exemptions = .py files, Python import-package dirs, vendored/third-party, lockfiles/generated output, tool-mandated filenames, frozen surfaces\"\n27:       - \"Fully reverses 027, including the sk-doc validator/loader logic keyed on feature_catalog / manual_testing_playbook\"\n28:       - \"Placement = top-level phase parent under sk-doc; packet number 020 (concurrent 032-smart-routing folds into 016); migration on a worktree\"\n29:       - \"Catalog-root transition = bounded dual-name tolerance + an explicit alias-removal phase\"\n30:       - \"Rename batching = dependency-closure (reference-graph SCCs), not per-extension\"\n31:       - \"node tooling in the worktree = fresh deterministic install, never a symlink to the main tree\"\n32: ---\n33: \n34: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n35: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 3 -->\n36: <!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/hvr_rules.md -->\n37: <!-- CONTENT DISCIPLINE: PHASE PARENT — root purpose + phase list + outcome; mechanics live in each child's plan.md, decisions in 001's decision-record.md. -->\n38: \n39: # Feature Specification: Repo-Wide Kebab-Case Filesystem Naming\n40: \n41: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n42: ## 1. METADATA\n43: \n44: | Field | Value |\n45: |-------|-------|\n46: | **Packet** | sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention |\n47: | **Level** | phase parent (Level 3) |\n48: | **Priority** | P1 |\n49: | **Status** | Planned |\n50: | **Created** | 2026-07-13 |\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 250. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Feature Specification: repo-wide kebab-case (hyphen) filesystem-naming convention\"\ndescription: \"Ban snake_case in filesystem names repo-wide and make kebab-case (hyphens) the sole canonical form for folder names, file names, and script filenames — with a hard exemption for Python (.py, PEP-8 snake_case) plus vendored/third-party trees, generated/lockfile output, tool-mandated filenames, and Python import-package directories. Code identifiers, JSON/YAML/TOML keys, frontmatter fields, and DB columns are OUT of scope (idiomatic case, hyphens illegal there). Reverses and supersedes the 027 underscore migration, including the sk-doc validator/loader logic keyed on feature_catalog / manual_testing_playbook. Phase parent for a 12-phase program (000-011): worktree + immutable-baseline + census first, then policy + all-consumer logic + create-generators + no-new-snake guard + rename-and-reference tooling + a frozen bijective rename map + shared cross-cutting closures, then a per-component migration fan-out, then alias-removal, the whole-repo gate, and integrate-latest + closeout. Migration runs on a dedicated worktree pinned to an immutable BASE SHA.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"hyphen naming convention\"\n  - \"kebab-case filesystem names\"\n  - \"ban snake_case files and folders\"\n  - \"reverse underscore migration\"\n  - \"hyphenate folder and file names\"\nimportance_tier: \"critical\"\ncontextType: \"planning\"\nparent: \"sk-doc\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-20T10:42:52Z\"\n    last_upd